description._content: Image Description from historic lecture booklet: "The weather, however, is most favorable for the growth of vegetation. For mile after mile along the rural road one may see great green hedges. These stand higher than a man's head even when clipped and trimmed. Land of Sentiment Ireland may be poor in physical resources but it is rich in human sentiment and spirit."
